Sperry Capital professionals offer clients direct experience in analysis, structuring and implementation of the full spectrum of financing tools.
sJames W. Martling, Principal and FounderSince founding Sperry Capital in 1994, Jim has advised numerous government and private clients across multiple sectors in California and national infrastructure projects. Jim has over 30 years of experience advising on infrastructure projects from conceptualization to financial closure.  The specific skill set includes project finance, express lanes structures and credits, public-private partnerships (P3), feasibility studies/financial projections, financial modeling, bid process strategy and management, financial structuring, debt and equity raising, contract structuring and negotiation support through financial closure.  Jim holds an A.B. degree from the University of California, Berkeley, an M.S. and M.B.A., Graduate School of Business from Columbia University, New York.Contact: jmartling@sperrycapital.comTelephone:  415.339.9201James H. Gibbs, PrincipalJim has over 30 years of experience in public finance  investment banking services.  He has managed multiple major financing transactions for water and sewer utilities, public power agencies, renewable energy corporations, transportation agencies, general municipal government, and non-profit corporations.  As regional manager for a national investment banking firm, he successfully completed several transactions for many large joint powers agencies making use of innovative project financing structures.  Prior to entering the consulting field, Jim joined the management team in charge of project development and capital finance planning for an emerging renewable fuel company (biosolids to fuel) utilizing an innovative waste water treatment technology.  Jim holds a Bachelor of Science (Electrical Engineering) from the University of California, Berkeley and an M.B.A. from the Graduate School of Business Stanford University, Stanford, California.Contact: jgibbs@sperrycapital.comTelephone: 415.339.9203T. Bryant Jenkins, PrincipalBryant has over 15 years of experience in providing infrastructure advisory services to a host of public and private sector clients.  His broad experience in financial modeling, public-private partnerships (P3), public finance, procurement support and business case development provide Sperry Capital's advisory teams with the valuable skill set required for today's complex infrastructure projects.  With extensive experience working for KPMG and UBS Securities,  Bryant frequently advises on the strategic, commercial and financial factors of  infrastructure projects.  His demonstrated ability to collaborate with relevant technical advisers and multiple stakeholders assists our clients in bringing their projects to completion. Bryant holds a Bachelor of Arts degree in Economics from Columbia University, New York and an M.B.A. from Stanford University's Graduate School of Business.Contact:  bjenkins@sperrycapital.comTelephone:  415.339.9204Garth A. Salisbury, PrincipalGarth has over 30 years of experience in infrastructure and utility investment banking.  During his tenure with major investment banks including Lehman Brothers, JPMorgan and Royal Bank of Canada, he structured over $35 billion of debt transactions for airports, housing agencies, electric, natural gas, water and wastewater entities throughout the US. He advised on the formation of the California Independent System Operator Corporation (electric transmission grid operator) and financed over $1 billion of projects for the CAISO.  Garth structured the largest transaction in the history of the tax-exempt market as senior book-running manager, the $11.3 billion California Department of Water Resources Power Purchase Program bond issue, during the California energy crisis.  Recognized for his highly technical structured finance skills, Garth assists Sperry Capital's client base to minimize their financing costs and to maximize their flexibility through innovative, tax-advantages finance plans.  His focus at Sperry also includes working with utilities and renewable energy companies to secure tax equity and private/bank financing for their projects.  Garth holds a Bachelor of Science degree in Finance and Economics from the University at Albany, New York.Contact:  gsalisbury@sperrycapital.comTelephone:  415-339-4441Martha J. Vujovich, PrincipalMartha has over 25 years of experience in commercial and investment banking, marketing,  financial advisory and investment of bond proceeds services including the development of investment and oversight policies for public agencies.  She has participated on Sperry Capital advisory teams for multiple new capital financing programs for first time borrowers, negotiating bank letters of credit in support of new debt financing and overseeing the introduction of new credits to the bond market.  Martha also works with several renewable energy clients interest in capital financing utilizing traditional and innovative funding options.  She holds a Bachelor of Arts degree from St. Olaf College, Northfield, Minnesota.Contact:  mvujovich@sperrycapital.comTelephone:  415-339-9202Lisa Amini, Principal ConsultantLisa has worked with Sperry Capital as a Principal Consultant since 2010.  She has over 19 years of experience providing advisory servies to major infrastructure projects around the world.  Previously, Lisa worked in London for InterGen, a prominent international independent power project developer, owned by Bechtel and Shell, where she led efforts in structuring and arranging large and complex project financings for independent power projects.  She also worked for Bechtel Enterprises, the ownership, development and financing arm of Bechtel, in San Francisco and in London, where she led efforts on the development and implementation of commercial and financial structures for a variety of large international projects, including infrastructure, power generation, oil and gas, and mining and metals projects.  She holds a Bachelor of Arts degree from the University of California, Santa Barbara, and an M.B.A. from the Haas School of Business (International Finance), University of California, Berkeley.  Lisa also serves as the Vice President and CFO for ADN Capital Ventures in Kentfield, California.Contact:  lamini@sperrycapital.comTelephone:  415.729.9193Steve Zimmerman, Principal ConsultantSteve joined Sperry Capital in 2015 after a long and distinguished career as Managing Director for the Western Region Office for Standard & Poor’s Ratings Services.  With over 30 years of credit risk evaluation and business development experience in all sectors of Public Finance, Steve is proficient at delivering sensitive communications and is known for his keen ability to quickly distill complex issues and focus on critical points that inform and expedite executive level decision making. His deep industry network encompasses leaders in Public Finance including institutional investors and financial intermediaries as well as pension funds and other corporate investors.Contact: szimmerman@sperrycapital.comTelephone: 415.250.4847Michelle Parra-Guedez, AssociateMichelle joined Sperry Capital in 2014 after graduating from Northeastern University with a B.S. in International Business.  Since joining our team, Michelle has gained extensive industry experience advising public sector clients.  Prior experience includes an investment banking internship at Bank of America Merrill Lynch where she was an analyst for the Public Finance team in San Francisco, focusing on capital structuring and bond underwriting.  Michelle also gained a year of capital markets experience while working for BNP Paribas Securities Services Division in Paris, France where she performed economic and market analyses of new sovereign credits using complex financial and demographic inputs.  She also assisted in the development of a unique project finance implementation of a cross-border project in Colombia.Contact:  mparra-guedez@sperrycapital.comTelephone:  415.887.9258













