Sperry Capital Inc. - Our Team











			Sperry Capital, Inc. Specializing in infrastructure and public finance advisory services.
		

			 
		

 









James W. Martling • James H. Gibbs • T. Bryant Jenkins • Martha J. Vujovich • Sperry R. Martling


Sperry R. Martling
Sperry Martling is an Analyst at Sperry Capital and has been with the firm since 2010. He provides financial modeling, quantitative analysis and strategic business case development services for the firm’s infrastructure advisory clients.
Mr. Martling is supporting the planning of a new capital financing program for a 501(c)(3) corporation in addition to providing technical analysis and support for the firm’s transportation clients. For the Orange County Transportation Authority, Mr. Martling provided technical analysis and back-up support for the issuance of the $293.54 M BABs and $59.03 M 2010 Series B Tax-Exempt Bonds. Mr. Martling also provided technical support for the issuance of the $100 M 91 Express Lanes Series 2010 private placement with the Orange County Investment Pool.
Mr. Martling has joined the financial advisory team to the California Department of Transportation on the Presidio Parkway P3 Project bringing quantitative analysis expertise to financial modeling and business case tasks. He also provides support for Sperry Capital’s public sector investment advisory clients, tracking performance and compliance to publicly mandated investment guidelines. 
Mr. Martling holds a B.A. degree in Economics from the University of California, at San Diego. He has completed continuing education coursework in advanced Microsoft Excel and quantitative analysis.










			(c) 2009 Sperry Capital, Inc.
		






Sperry Capital Inc. - Our Team











			Sperry Capital, Inc. Specializing in infrastructure and public finance advisory services.
		

			 
		

 









James W. Martling • James H. Gibbs • T. Bryant Jenkins • Martha J. Vujovich • Sperry R. Martling


James H. Gibbs
Jim Gibbs has over 35 years of experience in public finance consulting and investment banking. Prior to entering the consulting field, he was Managing Director and California Regional Manager of Public Finance for Lehman Brothers. Mr. Gibbs has successfully managed major financing transactions for renewable energy development corporations, transportation agencies, water and sewer utilities, public power agencies, general government, and 501(c)(3) nonprofit corporations. Mr. Gibbs leads the firmâs initiative in advising both large property owners and renewable energy project developers regarding the structuring and financing of renewable energy projects.
Working throughout his career from the San Francisco Bay Area, Mr. Gibbs brings his years of experience in public financing to the field of renewable energy project finance and development. By creating and analyzing opportunities for public sector participation in public private partnerships, Mr. Gibbs assists clients how best to optimize traditional municipal finance and private sector funding techniques.
As an investment banker and infrastructure financial advisor specializing in electric power generation, water and sewer and transportation public sector clients, Mr. Gibbs has brought over $50 billion in tax exempt new money bonds, including negotiated advance refundings, private placement offerings, fuel prepayment contracts and taxable subordinated debt and asset backed securities to market. In addition he has assisted many first time borrowers, working through the development process of seeking the best credit and financial structure to successfully issue bonds in the capital markets.  These have included advising a private corporation with new technology for converting biomass into fuel which successfully tax exempt, taxable and subordinated bonds and structuring an asset backed security for the financing of clean trucks.
Mr. Gibbs holds a Bachelor of Science degree from the University of California at Berkeley and a Master of Business degree from Stanford University










			(c) 2009 Sperry Capital, Inc.
		
















